SENATE RESOLUTION 272
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Rod Barnes on
receiving the 2025 National Association of
Agricultural Educators' Lifetime Achievement
Award.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body take great pleasure in recognizing
those dedicated educators who help the youth of Tennessee develop into responsible citizens
with bright futures in their chosen fields; and
WHEREAS, Rod Barnes is one of only six individuals to be honored by the National
Association of Agricultural Educators (NAAE) with the 2025 Lifetime Achievement Award; and
WHEREAS, founded upon the worthy mission of "professionals providing agricultural
education for the global community through visionary leadership, advocacy and service," the
NAAE bestows the Lifetime Achievement Award upon individuals who have retired from the
agricultural education profession and who contributed to the advancement of agricultural
education on a regional or national level throughout their careers; and
WHEREAS, after working in production agriculture for many years, Mr. Barnes began his
exemplary career in agricultural education at the age of forty-seven, thus bringing real-world
experience into the classroom; and
WHEREAS, during his nineteen-year tenure at McNairy Central High School, Mr. Barnes
built a thriving agricultural education program through which students earned State and national
recognition, developed successful greenhouse and sweet-corn enterprises, and benefited from
a new campus livestock learning center that he helped secure; and
WHEREAS, always committed to student success and giving back to his profession, Mr.
Barnes taught dual-credit agriculture courses, mentored future agricultural educators, and
established a scholarship endowment in honor of his son; and
SR0272
011532
- 1 -

WHEREAS, while his professional accomplishments are many, Mr. Barnes measures his
greatest success through the calls, visits, and messages from former students who credit him
with shaping their lives, an enduring testament to his impact as an educator, mentor, and
human being; and
WHEREAS, during his tenure at McNairy Central High School, Rod Barnes made a
tremendous positive impact through his leadership in developing future leaders in agriculture,
and he is worthy of our approbation upon his receipt of this prestigious honor; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and congratulate Rod
Barnes on receiving the 2025 National Association of Agricultural Educators' Lifetime
Achievement Award, applaud his commitment to agricultural education and the youth of his
community, and extend to him our best wishes for much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
